Closed with 120 For horses not nominated, supplementary nominations of $10,000 each will close at the time o f entry, Wednesday, September 6, 2023. All horses shall pay $4,500 additional to start, with $300,000 Guaranteed, of which $180,000 to first, $60,000 to second, $36,000 to third, $18,000 to fourth and $6,000 to fifth. Weight 123 lbs.; Non-winners of $50 ,000 allowed 3 lbs.; $30,000 other than claiming 5 lbs.; High weights preferred. Total non-claiming purse earnings will determine the order of preference for fillies of equal status. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. equal status. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAMARA bumped with rival at the start, gained prominent position outside early pacesetter, moved to the front while still in hand early on the bend then quickly kicked clear under no encouragement, padded that cushion into the stretch, stretched margin even further in the lane under light hand pressure and was ridden out to the wire in an extremely impressive performance. LAURENT broke out then reserved off early pace, chased from outside, five wide into bend, moved up four wide around the turn and into the stretch and moved well clear of others through the stretch. GATE TO PARADISE settled well off the rail, chased three wide then shifted out five wide exiting the turn and kicked away from others to clearly gain third. CHATALAS forwardly placed leaving the chute, stalked on two path then tracked between foes then outside foe while hard asked to remain close on the turn, continued on same path into the stretch and weakened a bit in final eighth. NEXT RIGHT THING ducked in early and dropped well back, recovered then chased along the rail before shifting three wide to the stretch and improved final placing. MOTET bumped with winner leaving the gate, chased from the outside, dropped back nearing the turn, remained well off the rail then five wide into the stretch and passed some tiring rivals late. PUSHINESS set pace down backstretch, had no resistance for TAMARA into far turn, remained along the rail and later weakened. JULIAS DREAM stalked from along the rail, remained inside and faded. BENEDETTA broke in a bit, chased from the inside and had to pause when crowded early, came off the fence, was two wide into the stretch and also weakened. PRETTY LAYLA reserved early from the inside, later came off the fence then three wide into the lane and lacked any rally. HOPE ROAD between rivals early, chased three wide early on the turn, came out further entering the stretch and lacked any response. CHEEKY GAL stalked from well of rail, chased four wide around the turn, came five wide into the stretch and also faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 11 1M Turf CR: 94. Maiden Special Weight Purse 82000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANDY MAN SHINES (IRE) angled in and chased on two path then between rivals, waited room nearing top of the stretch, shifted four wide for room, surged from outside, gained lead passing sixteenth marker and kicked clear. SPYCATCHER tracked pace from off the rail then three wide through the backstretch, bid in upper stretch, poked his nose in front for brief lead then had no answer for winner later in the drive but edged away for second. CALM SEA stalked from along the rail, continued inside into lane, was boxed in upper stretch, finally got clear nearing sixteenth marker and finished willingly. AUTOLINE (IRE) was off step slow, chased then along the rail, ran into some traffic at the top of the lane, came out some and finished with interest. BIGOFROMFRESNO outside rival into backstretch, continued two or three wide to the stretch and improved placing late. AARON crossed over and gained early control, set uncontested pace to final turn, resisted briefly when challenged into the stretch but weakened in final sixteenth. MY PARTNER GLEN reserved early, saved ground to last bend, came out three wide into the lane and lacked any response. BRING HIM HOME broke a step slow, lagged back while saving ground, remained inside, shifted out on last turn, came four wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. POP POP'S RIDE pulled early three wide, stalked while outside rival, continued three or four wide and weakened. TOKAMAK was closest pursuer to pacesetter into and through backstretch, between foes into the lane, lost contact in upper stretch and weakened.
